      <Composite Id="77bf903d-2db2-410e-9b21-3df9aaa00022">
        <MetaInfo Title="OnOff-Delay-Rcv" Description="OnOff-Delay with Rcv (28.05.2026)" Author="manni" LicenseAgreement="An incoming Rcv pulse is required to&#xD;&#xA;evaluate the input state.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Standard interlocked ON/OFF delay.&#xD;&#xA;The output switches to HIGH only&#xD;&#xA;after the input remains HIGH for the&#xD;&#xA;specified On-Delay time.&#xD;&#xA;To switch the output back to LOW, &#xD;&#xA;the input must remain LOW for the&#xD;&#xA;specified Off-Delay time.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;An incoming Rcv pulse is required to&#xD;&#xA;evaluate the input state.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Short signal fluctuations at the input&#xD;&#xA;are filtered out and do not affect&#xD;&#xA;the output.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;IN: I [Bit] (signal)&#xD;&#xA;IN: Rcv [Bit] (pulse)&#xD;&#xA;IN: On-Delay [sec]&#xD;&#xA;IN: Off-Delay [sec]&#xD;&#xA;OUT: O [Bit] (signal)&#xD;&#xA;OUT: Rcv [Bit] (pulse)&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;" Version="1.1" Keywords="" />
        <Content></Content>
      </Composite>
